A vanilla HTML/JS frontend communicates with a Flask backend (Python). The backend orchestrates a multi-phase AI pipeline: **extract → generate code → execute in sandbox → interpret results**. Authentication, file storage, and persistent data are handled by **Supabase** (Auth, Storage, PostgreSQL). LLM operations use the **Google Gemini 3.1 Flash Lite Preview** model.

**Recent major changes:**
- Complete UI revamp with new pink (#e95484) / navy (#2d2e3e) / beige (#f8f7f2) brand palette
- Custom illustrated characters for landing page (7 PNG assets)
- Chat pipeline deduplicated into shared `_run_analysis_pipeline()` generator
- Per-user DataFrame caching in `UserState` (prevents re-downloading from Supabase)
- Structured logging across all backend services
- Dead code removed (unused JS constants, duplicate CSS keyframes, legacy `script.js`)
- Landing page no longer loads unnecessary dashboard JS modules
- Pagination added to `/api/files` and `/api/chat/history` endpoints with shared `_paginate()` helper

