## 3. Code Execution Sandbox — Security Model

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    CODE[LLM-Generated<br>Python Code] --> LEN{Code Length<br>≤ 10,000 chars?}
    LEN -->|No| REJECT1[Rejected<br>Code too long]
    LEN -->|Yes| AST[AST Parsing<br>& Validation]
    AST -->|Blocked| REJECT[Rejected<br>Unsafe code detected]
    AST -->|Passed| SUB[Subprocess<br>Isolation via spawn]
    SUB --> SAFE["Safe Globals Only:<br>pandas, numpy, json"]
    SAFE --> TIMEOUT["60s Timeout Guard"]
    TIMEOUT -->|Success| NORM[Normalise Results<br>tables, charts, text, stats]
    NORM --> CONVERT[Deep Convert<br>numpy/pandas → native Python]
    TIMEOUT -->|Timeout| FAIL[TimeoutError]

    subgraph Blocked ["Blocked by AST Validator"]
        B1["Builtins (19): open, eval, exec,<br>compile, __import__, globals,<br>locals, getattr, setattr, delattr,<br>breakpoint, exit, quit, input,<br>memoryview, classmethod,<br>staticmethod, property, super"]
        B2["Modules (9): os, sys, subprocess,<br>socket, pathlib, shutil,<br>builtins, importlib, ctypes"]
        B3["Attributes (14): __class__, __bases__,<br>__dict__, __mro__, __subclasses__,<br>__globals__, __getattribute__,<br>__code__, __closure__, __func__,<br>system, popen, remove, unlink"]
    end
```

