## 6. Strengths

| # | Area | Details |
|---|------|---------|
| 1 | **Intelligent Multi-Phase Pipeline** | The 4-phase approach (extraction → code gen → execution → interpretation) is architecturally excellent. Instead of asking the LLM to analyse raw data (expensive and inaccurate), it generates executable pandas code, runs it in a sandbox, then has Gemini interpret computed results. This produces more accurate analyses at lower token cost. |
| 2 | **Deduplicated Pipeline** | `_run_analysis_pipeline()` is a shared generator function consumed by both `chat()` (non-streaming) and `chat_stream()` (SSE). Single source of truth for the entire analysis flow. |
| 3 | **Real Authentication & Multi-User Support** | Supabase Auth with email/password signup, JWT verification via `@require_auth` decorator on all API routes. Per-user `UserState` isolated by `user_id` from JWT. Thread-safe `SessionManager` with `threading.Lock`. |
| 4 | **Persistent Storage Layer** | Supabase PostgreSQL with `profiles`, `chat_sessions`, `dashboard_configs` tables and Row Level Security. File uploads stored in Supabase Storage with per-user directory isolation. Session rehydration on login. |
| 5 | **Sandbox Security (Defense-in-Depth)** | `code_executor.py` implements 5 layers: code length cap (10K chars), AST-based static analysis via `_SafetyVisitor`, 19 blocked builtins + 9 forbidden modules + 14 forbidden attributes, subprocess isolation via `spawn` context, and a 60-second timeout. |
| 6 | **Smart Data Profiling** | `data_service.py` auto-detects dataset types (survey, time series, transactional, categorical, numerical) and generates domain-specific analysis suggestions. Provides the LLM with richer context, significantly improving output quality. |
| 7 | **Token-Efficient Context Building** | Schema context is dynamically sized with a `max_tokens` budget. Correlations are computed locally, only metadata sent to the LLM. The extraction phase pulls out unique categorical values so the code generator knows exact column names — prevents hallucinated column references. |
| 8 | **Per-User DataFrame Caching** | Loaded DataFrames are cached in `UserState._file_cache` after first download. Schema contexts (lean + full) and data profiles are also cached per file. Invalidated on new upload. Prevents re-downloading from Supabase on every chat message. |
| 9 | **SSE Streaming Responses** | `/api/chat/stream` endpoint streams pipeline phases in real-time via Server-Sent Events. Frontend shows live progress updates (extracting → generating → executing → interpreting) instead of a static spinner. |
| 10 | **Graceful Degradation** | Code execution has 2 retry attempts with error feedback to Gemini, plus a text-only fallback (Phase 3). If code fails completely, users still get useful analysis. Cached results show a "Cached" badge for transparency. |
| 11 | **Polished UI with Custom Brand** | New pink/navy/beige brand palette with 7 custom illustrated character assets. Bento grid layout for landing page. Frosted glass input bars. Glassmorphic sidebar. Smooth micro-interactions (hover lifts, gradient avatars, animated typing dots). |
| 12 | **Full Dark Mode** | Complete `[data-theme="dark"]` overrides across all CSS files. Auto-detection via `prefers-color-scheme`. Theme toggle with localStorage persistence. Handsontable runtime color-scheme patching. |
| 13 | **Clean Modular CSS** | Stylesheets split into 5 concerns: `styles.css` (global/landing), `dashboard-layout.css`, `dashboard-chat.css`, `dashboard-grid.css`, `dashboard-overlays.css`. Imported via manifest (`dashboard.css`). CSS custom properties for all theming. |
| 14 | **Consistent Structured Logging** | All backend services use Python's `logging` module with named loggers (`data_talk`, `data_talk.auth`, `data_talk.gemini`). `_log_event()` emits structured JSON logs. Token usage tracked for all LLM calls. |
| 15 | **DOMPurify XSS Prevention** | All user-generated and LLM-generated markdown is sanitised through a `marked.js` → `DOMPurify` pipeline before DOM insertion. Custom `escapeHtml()` fallback if DOMPurify is unavailable. |
| 16 | **Per-User Query Caching** | LRU cache (300 items) per user prevents redundant API calls for repeated questions, saving both time and API costs. Thread-safe via `threading.Lock`. |
| 17 | **All Dependencies Pinned** | `requirements.txt` pins exact versions for all 10 packages — excellent for reproducibility and security. |
| 18 | **Easy Launch** | `start.bat` handles Python checks, dependency installation, server start, and browser launch in one click — low friction for non-technical users. |
| 19 | **Paginated List Endpoints** | `/api/files` and `/api/chat/history` support `?page=&per_page=` query parameters with metadata (`total`, `total_pages`). Shared `_paginate()` helper with configurable defaults via `app_config`. Backward-compatible — no params returns the first page. |

