## 7. Weaknesses

### 7.1 Critical Issues

| # | Area | Details | Location |
|---|------|---------|----------|
| 1 | **Thread-Unsafe Logout** | `logout()` mutates the shared Supabase singleton client's internal `_headers` attribute to inject user tokens before calling `sign_out()`. If two users log out simultaneously, headers can be interleaved. | `auth_service.py` lines 160-163 |
| 2 | **No Session Eviction** | `SessionManager._sessions` grows unboundedly as new users authenticate. No TTL or eviction policy. `remove_state()` exists but is never called (not invoked on logout). Long-running servers will leak memory. | `app_state.py` |
| 3 | **No Full Data Pagination** | `get_full_data()` loads the entire dataset into memory and sends it as JSON. No pagination. Large files will cause memory and bandwidth issues. (`/api/files` and `/api/chat/history` are now paginated — this only affects `/api/data/<filename>`.) | `server.py` lines 546-558 |

### 7.2 Security Concerns

| # | Area | Details | Location |
|---|------|---------|----------|
| 1 | **No Rate Limiting** | Chat, suggestion, and upload endpoints trigger expensive LLM calls. No throttling means easy API abuse/DoS. | `server.py` |
| 2 | **Zero SRI Hashes on All 6 CDN Resources** | Handsontable, SheetJS, Plotly.js, Marked.js, and DOMPurify all loaded without `integrity` or `crossorigin` attributes. A compromised CDN could inject arbitrary JavaScript with full access to auth tokens and data. | `dashboard.html` lines 15-23, 257 |
| 3 | **Unpinned CDN Versions** | SheetJS uses `xlsx-latest`, Handsontable and Marked.js use unpinned `npm/...` URLs. Supply-chain attack risk — malicious code could be injected via a version update with no safeguard. | `dashboard.html` |
| 4 | **localStorage Token Storage** | `dt_access_token`, `dt_refresh_token`, and `dt_user` stored in `localStorage`, accessible to any JS on the page including scripts from compromised CDNs. `httpOnly` cookies would be more secure. | `login.html` lines 349-351 |
| 5 | **No Prompt Injection Protection** | User questions are interpolated directly into LLM prompts. A crafted question could manipulate the system prompt, causing unintended code generation. | `gemini_service.py` |
| 6 | **Sandbox Escape Residual Risk** | While AST validation blocks known dangerous patterns, `type()`, `vars()`, `dir()`, and `hasattr()` remain in safe builtins. No memory or CPU limits on subprocess — malicious code could consume excessive resources. | `code_executor.py` |
| 7 | **No Token Refresh Endpoint** | The server returns `refresh_token` on login, but no endpoint exists to refresh an expired access token. Users must re-authenticate when tokens expire. | `auth_service.py` |
| 8 | **Token Verified via Network on Every Request** | `verify_token()` calls Supabase `getUser()` API on every authenticated request. No local JWT validation or caching. Adds latency and creates a dependency on Supabase availability. | `auth_service.py` line 130 |
| 9 | **Duplicate Supabase Config** | `SUPABASE_URL`, `SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`, and `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` are read independently in both `app_config.py` and `auth_service.py`. Inconsistency risk if only one is updated. | `app_config.py`, `auth_service.py` |

### 7.3 Performance Issues

| # | Area | Details | Location |
|---|------|---------|----------|
| 1 | **DataFrame Copied Per Execution** | Full DataFrame is `.copy()`'d for every code execution call — doubles memory for large files. | `code_executor.py` line 150 |
| 2 | **O(n^2) Correlation Computation** | Numeric correlation matrix computed for all column pairs — slow/expensive with 100+ columns. | `data_service.py` lines 188-205 |
| 3 | **Subprocess Per Query** | A new Python process is spawned via `multiprocessing.get_context("spawn")` for every single chat query. Process creation overhead adds 0.5-1s per request. | `code_executor.py` |
| 4 | **Particle Animation O(n^2)** | `connectParticles()` computes distance for every particle pair every frame. On 1920x1080: ~230 particles, ~26,000 comparisons per frame at 60fps. | `js/core.js` lines 261-286 |
| 5 | **Full Dashboard Grid Re-Render** | `renderDashboardGrid()` rebuilds entire grid HTML on every change (add, remove, reorder, resize), purging and re-creating all Plotly instances. | `js/dashboard-ui.js` |

### 7.4 Code Quality Issues

| # | Area | Details | Location |
|---|------|---------|----------|
| 1 | **Zero Test Coverage** | No unit tests, integration tests, or end-to-end tests for any component. The sandbox, data parsing, API endpoints, and auth are all untested. `.gitignore` includes `.pytest_cache/` but no tests exist. | Entire project |
| 2 | **Inconsistent Error Handling** | `server.py` returns structured JSON errors via `_error_response()`. `gemini_service.py` mixes return-error-dicts with raising `RuntimeError`. `code_executor.py` returns error dicts. `data_service.py` raises exceptions. No unified pattern. | All backend files |
| 3 | **No Module System (Frontend)** | All frontend functions are globals on `window` scope (~45+ functions). No ES modules, no bundler. Load order dependencies between files (e.g., `core.js` must load before `data-chat.js`). | All JS files |
| 4 | **No JSDoc / Minimal Docstrings** | Frontend functions have no documentation. Backend has minimal docstrings. Unclear parameter expectations across service boundaries. | All files |
| 5 | **Legacy `script.js` Still Exists** | `script.js` (16 lines) is a legacy module loader. No HTML file references it. Should be deleted. | `script.js` |
| 6 | **Duplicate CSS: Suggestion Chips** | `.suggestion-chip` / `.suggestions-row` defined in both `styles.css` (landing page) and `dashboard-chat.css` (dashboard). Minor inconsistencies in font-size (0.9rem vs 0.88rem). | CSS files |

### 7.5 UX / Accessibility Issues

| # | Area | Details |
|---|------|---------|
| 1 | **No Responsive Design for Dashboard** | Sidebar is fixed 260px with no collapse mechanism on mobile. Dashboard grid is always 3 columns. No responsive breakpoints. The app is desktop-only. |
| 2 | **Sidebar Nav Items Not Keyboard-Accessible** | Nav items use `<div onclick>` instead of `<button>` or `<a>`. Not focusable via Tab, no `role="button"`, no keyboard event handlers. |
| 3 | **No Skip Navigation Links** | No skip-to-content link for keyboard users. No ARIA live regions for error/success messages in login page. |
| 4 | **`alert()` / `confirm()` for User Feedback** | `removeDashChart()` and `clearAllCharts()` use browser `alert()`/`confirm()` dialogs. Blocks main thread and is inconsistent with the polished UI. |
| 5 | **Handsontable License** | Uses `"non-commercial-and-evaluation"` license key. Must verify this is appropriate for the intended use case. |
| 6 | **No ARIA Live Regions** | Login form error/success messages are not announced to screen readers. Status changes in chat (loading, phase updates) have no ARIA announcements. |

